ðŸ“Œ About the Project

This repository contains end-to-end Shell scripts to automate the deployment and management of the RoboShop microservices application based on a 3-Tier Architecture model.

The project focuses on real-world DevOps practices by using Bash scripting to install, configure, and manage frontend, backend services, and databases on Linux servers (AWS EC2).

ðŸ—ï¸ Architecture Overview (3-Tier)

The application is designed using a 3-Tier Architecture, which separates concerns for better scalability, security, and maintainability.
---------------------------------------------------------------------

1ï¸âƒ£ Frontend Tier

Technology: Nginx

Serves static web content

Acts as a reverse proxy

Communicates with backend services via APIs

2ï¸âƒ£ Backend Tier (Microservices)

Each backend service is deployed and managed using individual shell scripts:

Catalogue â€“ Product information service

User â€“ User authentication & profiles

Cart â€“ Shopping cart operations

Shipping â€“ Order shipment processing

Payment â€“ Payment transactions

Services are managed using systemd service files

3ï¸âƒ£ Database / Messaging Tier

MongoDB â€“ Catalogue & User data

Redis â€“ Cart & session storage

MySQL â€“ Shipping data

RabbitMQ â€“ Message queue for async communication (Payment â†’ Dispatch)

